Title:     A very powerful PIM that's no picnic to learn.
             (personal information management system)  (Ecco Professional
             1.1)
Author:    Haskin, David


Abstract:  Arabesque Software's $395 Ecco Professional 1.1 is one of the
           most powerful personal information managers (PIM) available,
           but its learning curve is steep. It offers exceptional
           flexibility via a customizable toolbar, templates,
           auto-dialing and other high-end features. There are three
           interrelated views: a phone book, a calendar and an outliner
           module. The calendar has an attached to-do list and lets users
           look at schedules by day, week or month. Both the phone book
           and calendar have outlining capabilities of their own. There
           are columns for storing additional information about each item
           and adapting the program to specific needs. Ecco's basic
           features are easy to master, but its advanced capabilities are
           difficult to learn because of the sheer number of options and
           complex relationships among the three views. The package
           supports Object Linking and Embedding but not Dynamic Data
           Exchange; connectivity with other programs is very good.
